summary: The script reads two CSV files containing FID scores and CLIP scores, merges the data, and creates a scatter plot of FID versus CLIP values. Each data point is annotated with its configuration identifier, and the resulting figure is displayed for visual analysis.
business_intent: Enable researchers and engineers to quickly assess and compare the performance of text-to-image models by visualizing the trade-off between image fidelity (FID) and semantic similarity (CLIP) across different model configurations.
